track_notes: Parked on the park loop rd area for access to Champlain ridge trail. Awesome ocean views from summit.

This is a route up Champlain Mountian from the Northwest, using Beachcroft Path.
Use the parking area just south of the Sieur de Monts entrance on Route 3.
Then walk south on route 3 to the Beachcroft trailhead. The first part of the trail is well built, but as you round Huguenot Head, it starts getting serious about gaining height, and for us old, out of shape people is a bit of a challenge. I dont suppose a 50lb backpack helps.
Nice views from the top. Found a place to operate, out of the way, a short distance to the west of the summit, and was not disturbed. Lots of people.
track_title: Route to Champlain Mountain from Sieur de Mont
